    {
      "source": "discord",
      "time": "2026-05-01T01:37:58.543000+00:00",
      "lang": "",
      "title": "[DC] sirtealot@🔸有問必答┊official-q-a: As a continuation of my Pandia post (which didn't fit due to the character limit",
      "summary": "As a continuation of my Pandia post (which didn't fit due to the character limit), I'd also like to offer some suggestions regarding Casiah, who is another character I'm very passionate about  \n\nCasiah's current standing in the game is considerably better than Pandia's, and I am very happy about the strength generation buffs she's receiving, but I'd still like to use the 2.5.1 buffs as a potential opportunity to address her passive \"Master of Magic\". \n\nIt currently increases Casiah's base damage based on her personal Realm Mastery stat whenever she unleashes exalt, which is not a particularly useful effect on a character with low damage and no additional multipliers in her kit. It also doesn't synergize with the temporary strength she generates. Due to these reasons, here are some potential ideas:\n\n- If the intention is to make Casiah into a supportive damage dealer, then perhaps the passive could give her a smaller amount of final damage scaling instead, so that the strength is accounted for.\n\n- Alternatively, it could make her exalt and/or Telekinesis enjoy a bigger strength bonus based on the Realm Mastery she has.\n\n- If Casiah is to remain a pure support, then perhaps her passive could slowly scale up the amount of strength she generates based on Realm Mastery.\n\n- As another idea, it could apply a small amount of temporary strength reduction on enemies based on the strength Casiah generates, with the scaling being impacted by Realm Mastery.\n\n- Or it could simply refund a part of her exalt cost per each point of Realm Mastery.\n\nOnce again, thank you for reading through my suggestions!! ",
      "url": "https://discord.com/channels/1131791637933199470/1499585644249481278/1499585644249481278",
      "author": "sirtealot",
      "engagement": 24,
      "metadata": {
        "reactions": "Casiah_gift×8",
